Ubuntu 16.04.3 Server amd64
---------------------------

2018-02-07:         (Adam Vail <avail@sandia.gov>)

  o   Initial install with no networking from ubuntu-16.04-beta2-server-amd64.iso
                      - qemu-img made with 100GB max size
                      - normal install selected, defaults used everywhere with username
                        / password ubuntu / ubuntu
                      - mountain time zone selected
                      - guided, use entire disk was selected (no LVM)
                      - no HTTP proxy was selected
                      - no automatic updates were selected
                      - OpenSSH server was selected to be installed
  o   Set timeout for dhcp to 10 in /etc/dhcp/dhclient.conf
  o   Temporarily added wwwproxy.sandia.gov:80 to /etc/apt/apt.conf and installed,
                            python2.7
                            python-netaddr
        Then cleared the cached debs in /var/cache/apt/archive
  o   Copied over the qmeu-ga-patched-static to /usr/sbin
        and put the qemu-guest-agent.service systemd script in /etc/systemd/system/
  o   The guest agent needs /usr/local/var/run to exist:
        sudo mkdir -p /usr/local/var/run
  o   Make the qemu-guest-agent service run on startup:
        sudo systemctl enable qemu-guest-agent.service

2018-07-30:         (Christopher Cordi <cncordi@sandia.gov>)
  o   This image is no used for xenial servers (replaced by 16.04.4-server-amd64)

Ubuntu 16.04.4 Desktop amd64
----------------------------

2018-07-24:         (Christopher Cordi <cncordi@sandia.gov>)

  o   Same steps as above but with ubuntu-16.04.4-desktop-amd64.iso
  o   Ran apt-get purge of networkmanager* and network-manager*
  o   Set resolution to 1280x1024
  o   Copied /etc/network/interfaces from a fresh Ubuntu 16.04.4 server, but changed source to source-directory.

2018-07-27:         (Christopher Cordi <cncordi@sandia.gov>)
  o   Shrunk qc2 file as follows
        Did initial install on a 10 GB qc2.
        Allocated all zero file with rest of vm space: dd if=/dev/zero of=/tmp/zero_file; sync; rm /tmp/zero_file; sync
        qemu-img convert <original_vm>.qc2 -O qcow2 <shrunk_vm>.qc2 # create new qc2 only slightly larger than currently
            allocated space in vm
        qemu-img resize <shrunk_vm>.qc2 +90G # resize guest disk space to 100G

2018-07-30:         (Christopher Cordi <cncordi@sandia.gov>)
  o   This image has been converted to qcow2 from raw and recompressed
2018-10-08:         (Christopher Cordi <cncordi@sandia.gov>)
  o   Change resolution to 1280x1024
  o   Fixed VM partition to be 100GB

